result.execSummary:
Shaunte Kelly was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Shaunte Kelly was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Shaunte Kelly in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has been extradited to the state of Illinois.  On motion of the state, court ordered case administratively closed.

Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court, defendant Shaunte Kelly not in court, in custody.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom.  Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court. Case remains calendared for status conference 08-09-2022 at 8:30 am, ICCR.

Defendant Shaunte Kelly in court with attorney Corey R. Flynn.  Defendant Shaunte Kelly in custody.  Anthony White appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Shaunte Kelly appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 2.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of ILLINOIS.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Defense requests bail hearing before trial court to address remand.   Bail/bond hearing scheduled for July 22, 2022 at 08:30 am.  Status conference scheduled for August 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.
